Romantha Botha, Netwerk24Nicola Pienaar (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Jaco Oosthuizen, 31, who&nbsp;appeared in the&nbsp;Paarl Magistrate's Court&nbsp;for the murder of Nicola Pienaar, 28, was&nbsp;denied bail&nbsp;on Tuesday.Netwerk24 reported that Magistrate Diane Blaauw said Oosthuizen could not prove extraordinary circumstances to the court as to why he&nbsp;should be released on bail. He also did not have a fixed address. Oosthuizen is charged for allegedly burying Pienaar in a&nbsp;shallow grave in January. Her uterus had been cut open and a foetus&nbsp;had been&nbsp;found outside her body. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.